gate: OPEN
sprint: S05
track: A
task: A2
title: "fix(delivery): persist UPS OAuth token across Cloud Run instances"
repos: [crop-parts-services]
priority: high
refs:
  - S02 hypothesis B — ups-oauth.ts:27, instance-memory token lost on cold start
  - S02 lesson: ups_oauth_cache
requires: [BUN_HONO_CLOUDRUN, SECURITY]

description: |
  UPS OAuth token stored in instance memory only. On Cloud Run cold start or
  scale-out the token is lost — first XAV call on that instance pays +300–500ms
  for a new OAuth round-trip. Fix: persist token in a shared cache (Memorystore
  Redis or equivalent). Token must be encrypted at rest, TTL 3300s (< UPS 3600s expiry).

ground_truth:
  file: CROP-parts-services/services/delivery/src/providers/ups/ups-oauth.ts
  line: 27   # in-memory token store

scope:
  in:
    - ups-oauth.ts — replace instance-memory with shared cache read/write
    - Cache backend proposal documented in PR (Memorystore vs other)
    - TTL: 3300s (safe margin under UPS 3600s expiry)
    - Unit test: cache miss → fetch + store; cache hit → skip OAuth round-trip
  out:
    - XAV result caching (A3)
    - Any crop-front changes

invariants:
  - Token is a credential — never logged, never in Sentry breadcrumbs
  - TTL must be < UPS token expiry

acceptance:
  - Warm instance: OAuth skips network call (cache hit in test)
  - Cold instance: token fetched once, stored, subsequent calls hit cache
  - Token never appears in logs or error bodies

dep: A1
output: ups-oauth.ts + cache adapter + unit tests + infra note in PR
